{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6b103bb4-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s59q–1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"59q–1"},"text":"§ 59q–1.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Union Canal, Outer Buffalo Harbor, New York","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The portion of the Union Canal, also known as the Union Ship Canal, an appendage of the Buffalo Outer Harbor, located in the City of Buffalo, State of New York, is declared to be a nonnavigable waterway of the United States within the meaning of the General Bridge Act of 1946 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s525"},"text":"33 U.S.C. 525","children":[],"tail":", et seq.) from a point two hundred feet west of Fuhrmann Boulevard east to its terminus."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6b103bb5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/202/s101"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–202, § 101","children":[],"tail":"("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":") [title III, § 332], "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-22"},"text":"Dec. 22, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1329-358"},"text":"101 Stat. 1329–358","children":[],"tail":", 1329–384.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6b103bb6-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6b103bb7-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id6b103bb8-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The General Bridge Act of 1946, referred to in text, is title V of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-08-02/ch753"},"text":"act Aug. 2, 1946, ch. 753","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/847"},"text":"60 Stat. 847","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to subchapter III (§ 525 et seq.) of chapter 11 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s525"},"text":"section 525 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
